OL,3,CTeacher unions to ballot members on
OL,4,Ctaking industrial action over pay
OL,6,F"Despite promises from our politicians
OL,7,Fand decision-makers to ensure our
OL,8,Fteachers are equally valued, the
OL,9,Fmarked lack of progress and commitment
OL,10,Fhere is causing grave concern.
OL,12,F"We call on the minister to address
OL,13,Fthis issue as a matter of priority,
OL,14,Frestore the pay to fair and equitable
OL,15,Flevels, and allow us to move forward."
